&lt;p&gt;Lake Harriet Veterinary seeks an experienced Certified Veterinary Technician for a Full-Time position at our 7 doctor practice. We are looking for a self-motivated, team player to join our inclusive, talented team consisting of 30 employees. Applicants must be kind, respectful of staff and clients, and ready to work in a busy practice. We provide flexible scheduling and close early on Fridays at 4:00pm and at 12:00pm on Saturdays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here at LHV, our CVT&#39;s rotate through different roles throughout the week. These roles include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Running our laboratory including in-house diagnostics and outgoing lab sample processing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Managing technician appointments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Supporting a DVM in appointments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Assisting in surgery including&amp;nbsp;preparation, anesthesia,&amp;nbsp;dental prophylaxis&amp;nbsp;and dental radiographs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Providing support for the entire treatment area staff in our Float position&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Come work alongside our highly skilled team with goals of providing excellent care to both our clients and patients every day!&amp;nbsp;We have curated a supportive space with low turnover that promotes a healthy work-life balance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information about our hospital, please visit lakeharrietvet.com&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
