&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Certified Veterinary Technician in Baxter, MN&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Voted Best in the Area for Veterinary Clinics and Grooming Facilities,&lt;a href=&quot;https://animalcarecenterbaxter.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Animal Care Center&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is seeking a full-time or part-time Certified Veterinary Technician (CVT) to join our collaborative 3-doctor team in Minnesota&#39;s beautiful Brainerd Lakes Area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&#39;re looking for a hospital where technicians are trusted, respected, and utilized to their full potential, you&#39;ll feel right at home here. We maintain an exceptional 2:1 technician-to-doctor ratio, allowing our team to focus on delivering outstanding patient care while practicing advanced technical skills. Our technicians play an integral role in anesthesia and surgery, including inducing anesthesia, intubating patients, monitoring procedures, and managing dedicated technician appointments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe work-life balance is just as important as quality medicine. Our hospital is open Monday through Friday from 8:00 AM to 5:00 PM, no regular evenings, weekends, or holiday shifts. Full-time technicians are scheduled either four days or five days each week and enjoy a full one-hour lunch break every shift.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For those interested in additional earning opportunities, technicians may participate in our after-hours emergency on-call program from 5:00 PM to 10:00 PM on weekends. Team members receive an on-call stipend plus a minimum of two hours of time-and-a-half pay whenever called into the hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Animal Care Center, you&#39;ll be part of a professional, supportive team dedicated to providing exceptional medical, surgical, and dental care while helping technicians grow their skills and build rewarding long-term careers.&lt;/p&gt;
